line_1: Talk with such toss, and saunter with such swing;
line_2: Join'd with these powers, he could so sweetly sing,

line_1: As some of those who in a hammock swing.
line_2: With as good observation of the thing

line_1: Then stooped on flexile twig to swing,
line_2: Then rose aloft with outspread wing,

line_1: And may they soon at Tyburn swing,
line_2: Who would not sign what here I sing.

line_1: "And while this rogue is doom'd in air to swing,
line_2: " That for a peerage kneels to thank the King. "
